      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): disable thinking for minimax-m3 anthropic-messages path",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nMinimax models using the Anthropic Messages path through opencode-go return\nthinking content as regular text blocks rather than proper `type:\"thinking\"`\nAnthropic blocks. Without disabling thinking at the request level, internal\nreasoning leaks to channel output.\n\nThis adds a stream wrapper that injects `thinking: { type: \"disabled\" }`\nfor minimax-m3 models, preventing reasoning leakage.\n\n## Changes\n\n`extensions/opencode-go/stream.ts`: Add `createOpencodeGoMinimaxNoThinkingWrapper`\nthat identifies minimax-m3 models and injects disabled thinking into the\nrequest payload. The wrapper is inserted before the existing Kimi and\nDeepSeek wrappers in the chain.\n\n## Evidence\n\nVitest:\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/opencode-go/\n\n Test Files  5 passed (5)\n      Tests  28 passed (28)\n```\n\n**Label**: bug\n\n_AI-assisted._",
